<th>Description</th>
<td>Item is an Egyptian well originally used to measure the height of the Nile. Constructed by Ramesses the Great, it was refurbished by the Roman Emperor Hadrian in the 2nd Century AD. This item can be used to reverse aging and cure chronic illnesses; use requires the sacrifice of an individual close to the user.</td>
